RIBAVIRIN, AVAILABILITY (07)
============================
Date: Tue, 29 Apr 1997 15:28:00 -0400
From: Scott Halstead <halsteads@MAIL-GW.NMRDC.NNMC.NAVY.MIL>
[see
Ribavirin, availability 970308151829
Ribavirin, availability (02) 970311145128
Ribavirin, availability (03) 970324103535
Ribavirin, availability (04) 970326134846
Ribavirin, availability (05) 970329124321
Ribavirin, availability (06) 970428101529]
Congratulations to Charlie Calisher for raising the troubling issue of the
expense and general unavailability of ribavirin, a life-saving drug needed
in West Africa. I gave a fair amount of thought to this problem while I
was at the Rockefeller Foundation, but did not move as far as I had hoped.
1. We discovered that ribavirin is manufactured in China (possibly not
under ICN license) where it is rather inexpensive.
2. This is a problem which the WHO Regional Office for Africa needs
to address. This is a perfect opportunity for one or more donor countries
make funds available to purchase ribavirin, reduce Lassa mortality and make
an important humanitarian statement.
3. UNICEF has a relevant program called the Bamako Initiative
(I believe) in which soft currencies go into a UNICEF account to pay for
local programs while UNICEF uses hard currency to purchase pharmaceuticals
on the open market. How much of the Lassa morbidity and mortality is in
children?
---
Scott B. Halstead
e-mail: <halsteads@mail-gw.nmrdc.nnmc.navy.mil>
